What Spatz is refering to when he mocks your pride and honor is that he would like everyone to be like him, sorely without either.  Misery loves company and he desperately needs it.<br>
Spatz is eaten up with idealism.  It appears that he loves the enemy and that is all it takes to turn the tide of physical force.  He is so busy transmitting his face saving, draft dodging garbage that he cannot pick up anything on his receiver.<br>
Your example of &quot;pride and honor,&quot; that of the Corps and everybody else who served will cost American lives as always.  However, pride and honor on our part as a nation will cost the aggressor far more lives... causing them to think twice before they threaten free institutions.<br>
Wars won't go away because people don't like them.  Wars are held in abeyance because one side is filled up with young men (like U.S. Marines) with a inexhaustible sense of pride and honor who will put you in a world of hurt if you threaten freedom.<br>
Your style of pride and honor, an ongoing trait of Marines, Sailors, Airmen and Soldiers reassures me that a few youngsters are acquiring those same values even as we speak and that they, like you, will go forth when needed to protect two old warriors like us, our children and our grandchildren.<br>
Don't worry about Spatz.  He will never get a handle on you.<br>
He can't even get a handle on himself.  Spatz needs to go on the street and pass out dog biscuits to rabid mad dogs.  Maybe he could learn to temper idealism with a little dose of realism.  In the meantime, keep your pride and honor up high where I can see it, &quot;Bro.&quot;<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
